						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in a field to the south of Mallēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>9th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated record can be assigned to 9th century A.D., on the basis of palaeography and internal evidences.</p>						

						<p>Fragmenentary. Refers to Lonkuḷāditya and a fight between a [chief (Sāmaṭṭi-Sāmanta)] vāṇarāju and certain Rāpulinoṇḍu, propably a title to the Uncle <hi rend="italic">(māma)</hi> of Lonkuḷāditya.</p>						

						</summary>
